Class Key

  • java.lang.Object
    • Key

  • public class Key
extends java.lang.Object
    This class represents a key on the keyboard of a piano that can play a note.
    Author:
    Jocelyn

      Key(int midi, org.jfugue.realtime.RealtimePlayer play)
      Creates a key that plays the note with the midi number provided and plays the key using the player passed in.

    • Method Detail

      • play

        public void play()
        Starts playing the note if it is not already playing. If the note is already playing, lets the note continue playing but does not replay the note.

      • stop

        public void stop()
        Stops playing the note if it is currently playing.
